**Final Verdict**: [ALL PASS / REVISIONS RECOMMENDED]
```

### Step 4: Return Findings
Hand off findings report to the orchestrator (400) or user.

**Do NOT auto-fix stories in Jira.** Validation only. PM decides whether to fix now or proceed.

## Quality Levels

### PASS (No Action Required)
- All INVEST principles met
- 2-4 well-structured BDD scenarios
- Workday context is accurate
- Editorial quality is high
- Jira format is correct

### FLAGS (Minor Issues, Optional Fix)
- Small wording improvements possible
- Non-critical formatting inconsistencies
- Nice-to-have Workday context additions
- Story is still shippable as-is

### NEEDS REVISION (Action Required)
- INVEST principles violated (not independent, too large, not testable)
- Missing or poor BDD scenarios (<2 scenarios, inline clauses, no error cases)
- Incorrect Workday terminology or workflow misunderstanding
- Legal-sensitive copy without 060 review
- Jira format issues (missing AC table, wrong epic link)

## Common Anti-Patterns to Flag

| Anti-Pattern | Validation Check | Recommended Fix |
|---|---|---|
| Technical task instead of user story | INVEST: Not Valuable | Reframe as user story with outcome |
| Story too large (>8 points) | INVEST: Not Small | Apply SPIDR splitting framework |
| Only 1 scenario or no error scenarios | BDD: Insufficient coverage | Add error/edge case scenarios |
| Gherkin clauses on same line | BDD: Format violation | Move each clause to NEW LINE |
| Vague acceptance criteria | INVEST: Not Testable | Add specific BDD scenarios |
| Incorrect Workday terminology | Workday Context | Fix using Deployment Agent guidance |
| Generic error messages | Editorial Quality | Apply 319 error pattern (problem + solution) |
| Missing value slice label | Format: Jira config | Add VS1/VS2/VS3 label |
| No epic link | Format: Jira config | Link to epic key |

